parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause fires, engine stalling, and loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
smoke is emitted from the engine compartment
the engine stalls while driving
the headlights remain on after turning off the ignition
the ignition switch becomes warm or hot
the power goes off and on
and the electrical wires melt or burn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition switch failures can cause fires, engine stalling, and loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The ignition switch becomes warm or hot
the ignition switch sticks
the ignition switch fails
and the electrical wires melt or burn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alternator failures can cause fires, engine stalling, and loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The alternator plug melts
the alternator causes an underhood fire
and the electrical wires melt or burn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can lead to a loss of restraint, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle fails to latch
the seat belt buckle breaks
the seat belt buckle comes loose while driving
the seat belt buckle does not hold
the seat belt buckle fails to stay latched
the seat belt retractor falls out of track.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control switch can cause the vehicle to catch fire, resulting in property damage and potentially serious injury or death.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
often under the hood
even when turned off and parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Acceleration due to Cruise Control or TPS Switch Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden acceleration of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as well as property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning
even when the brakes are applied
and may cause loss of control or collision.
